The six strains (Table 1) were cultivated in bioreactors each as triplicate. Minimal medium with defined composition was used in the cultivation to enable accurate measurement of the nutrients taken up and the compounds produced as needed for stoichiometric modelling. Cellobiose was used as an inducing carbon source [9] and ammonium sulfate as the source of nitrogen in the cultures. The cultures were extensively monitored both off- and on-line (Figs. 1, 2). CO\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
