In addition to the extracellular variables, we measured the concentration of intracellular free amino acids from the 24, 40 and 64 h sampling time points (Additional file 1: Figure S3). Overall, they exhibited a decreasing trend during cultivation. Exceptions to this trend were often associated with larger deviation between repeats or with small concentrations. Over 1000 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
